{{Infobox person | name = Olufemi Oguntamu | image = | caption = | birth_date = {{birth date and age|df=yes|1990|12|17}} | birth_place = [[Lagos]], [[Lagos State]], Nigeria | nationality = [[Nigerian]] | education = | alma_mater = | occupation = Social media strategist, entrepreneur, founder and Lead Consultant of Penzaarville | years_active = 2014-present | known_for = "Handle it Africa" | notable_works = Penzaarville, Handle it Africa | awards =
}}
'''Olufemi Oguntamu''' popularly known as '''Penzaar''', is a Nigerian Social Media Strategist, the founder and lead consultant of Penzaarville, an agency that specializes in social media management, marketing and brand promotion based in Lagos, Nigeria.<ref name="ThisDay">{{cite news|title=Olufemi Oguntamu: It's No Longer a Joke; My Efforts on the Social Media are Being Noticed|url=https://www.thisdaylive.com/index.php/2017/07/29/olufemi-oguntamu-its-no-longer-a-joke-my-efforts-on-the-social-media-are-being-noticed/|website=This Day|accessdate=8 September 2018}}</ref>
==Early life and education==
Oguntamu was born in Surulere, Lagos, Nigeria to Olugbenga Oguntamu, an Educationist and Oluseyi Oguntamu, A Civil servant. Oguntamu attended primary school at Effortswill Schools and attended Secondary School at Excel College, Ejigbo, Lagos. In 2008, he got admission into Olabisi Onabanjo University(OOU) where he studied Mass communication and attained a Bachelor of Arts in Mass communication, graduating in 2012.
==Career== In 2014, Oguntamu began working with RED Media as an intern in the projects department, he later went further to work for Media Crafts Associate as a Social media manager while he also worked as a freelance at Smackers limited where he handled the online community for ''The Place Nigeria''.
===Penzaarville=== Oguntamu founded his own Social Media Company, Penzaarville in September, 2015 which then kicked full operations as an Agency in November, 2016.<ref>{{cite news|title=I can never post nude pictures online even if I’m paid $1m –Penzaar|url=https://punchng.com/can-never-post-nude-pictures-online-even-im-paid-1m-penzaar/|website=Punch Newspaper|accessdate=8 September 2018}}</ref>
Penzaarville has worked on a number of social media projects and as a brand influencer for a number of notable firms including Google Nigeria, Microsoft Nigeria, MTN, Nokia, Taxify, Pepsi and Wema Bank.<ref>{{cite web|title=Nigerian Social Media Influencers and Bloggers making things Happen in the Digital Era|url=http://www.bennycapricorn.com/nigerian-social-media-influencers-and-bloggers-making-things-happen/|website=Benny Capricon|accessdate=8 September 2018}}</ref><ref name = "Thisday">{{cite news|title=Penzaarville Celebrates, Recounts Contribution to Media Industry |url=https://www.thisdaylive.com/index.php/2018/11/02/penzaarville-celebrates-recounts-contribution-to-media-industry/|website=Thisday newspaper|accessdate=3 November 2018}}</ref>
===Handle It Africa=== In 2017, Oguntamu founded a Social Media Conference “Handle It Africa” to bridge the gap between innovation, communication, and development.<ref>{{cite news|title="We are going to use social media to drive change" - Olufemi Oguntamu|url=https://www.pulse.ng/news/tech/handle-it-africa-we-are-going-to-use-social-media-to-drive-change-olufemi-oguntamu-id6500012.html|website=PulseNG|accessdate=8 September 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=We will use social media to drive change – Olufemi Oguntamu|url=https://dailytimes.ng/will-use-social-media-drive-change-olufemi-oguntamu/|website=Daily Times Newspaper|accessdate=8 September 2018}}</ref>
The event was well reported upon in Nigeria as it drew attendance from a wide range of online media professionals, featuring platforms for panel discussions as well as networking and ideas-sharing. <ref>{{cite news|title= Handle it Africa… New social media conference comes on stream|url=https://guardian.ng/saturday-magazine/handle-it-africa-new-social-media-conference-comes-on-stream/|website=The Guardian Newspaper|accessdate=8 September 2018}}</ref> It is considered one of the most influential social media conferences in Nigeria. <ref name = "Thisday"/>
