'''Tymberlee Hill''' is an American actress and comedian, best known for her roles on comedy programs such as ''[[Marry Me (U.S. TV series)|Marry Me]]'', ''[[Drunk History]]'', ''[[The Hotwives]]'' and ''[[Search Party (TV series)|Search Party]]''.
==Career== Hill grew up in [[Virginia Beach, Virginia]]. In 2003, she received her graduate degree from the Shakespeare Theatre's Academy for Classical Acting at [[George Washington University]].<ref name="ucb">{{cite web|title=Tymberlee Hill|url=http://ucbcomedy.com/user/17924|work=UCB Comedy|accessdate=May 14, 2017}}</ref> A classically trained stage actor, Hill started performing in comedy after moving to [[Los Angeles]] and beginning to perform at the [[Upright Citizens Brigade Theatre]].<ref>{{cite web|last1=Popkin|first1=Jeremy|title=Inside 'Marry Me,' 'Hotwives,' and 'Drunk History' with Tymberlee Hill|url=http://splitsider.com/2014/09/inside-marry-me-hotwives-and-drunk-history-with-tymberlee-hill/|date=September 22, 2014|work=Splitsider|accessdate=May 14, 2017}}</ref>
She continues to perform at the UCB Theatre.<ref name="ucb"/> In 2014, Hill began playing the role of Phe Phe Reed in the [[Hulu]] sitcom ''[[The Hotwives]]''.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Portwood|first1=Jerry|title= 10Qs: Tymberlee Hill on Hotwives, Casey Wilson & Meeting NeNe Leakes|url=http://www.out.com/television/2015/8/18/tymberlee-hill-hotwives-casey-wilson-meeting-nene-leakes|date=August 18, 2015|work=Out Magazine|accessdate=May 14, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=Bierly|first1=Mandi|title=Watch the women of 'Hotwives of Orlando' judge each other|url=http://ew.com/article/2014/07/17/hotwives-of-orlando-casey-wilson/|date=July 17, 2014|work=Entertainment Weekly|accessdate=May 14, 2017}}</ref> In 2014, Hill was cast in the [[NBC]] comedy series ''[[Marry Me (U.S. TV series)|Marry Me]]'' as a series regular, playing the role of Kay until the series' cancellation after one season.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Andreeva|first1=Nellie|title=Amanda Detmer Joins ABC's 'Sea Of Fire'; Tymberlee Hill Added To NBC's 'Marry Me'|url=http://deadline.com/2014/02/amanda-detmer-joins-abcs-sea-of-fire-tymberlee-hill-added-to-nbcs-marry-me-688394/|date=February 24, 2014|work=Deadline|accessdate=May 14, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=Rafus|first1=Eboni|title=Tymberlee Hill praises her "Marry Me" love interest, Ana Ortiz|url=http://www.afterellen.com/tv/409129-tymberlee-hill-praises-marry-love-interest-ana-ortiz|date=January 14, 2015|work=AfterEllen|accessdate=May 14, 2017}}</ref> She has a recurring role as Detective Joy on season two of the TBS mystery-comedy ''[[Search Party (TV series)|Search Party]]''.
